The paper deals with robotics and machine learning for autonomous manipulation of objects, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves simulating interaction with objects in the scene, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The use of machine learning for manipulation strategies indicates the involvement of both artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application scenarios of logistics and retail suggest the involvement of systems and control (cs.SY).
